14:59.198 --> 15:00.414
- [CAR DOOR CLOSES]
- Nice and easy.

15:00.416 --> 15:02.297
- [GUN COCKS]
- Put the fucking gun down!

15:02.299 --> 15:03.472
Put the fucking gun down.

15:03.474 --> 15:04.494
No, no, no! Listen to me.

15:04.497 --> 15:05.866
- I'm a private investigator.
- Do it!

15:05.868 --> 15:08.494
I've got identification.

15:08.497 --> 15:11.471
On your knees. Now.

15:11.474 --> 15:12.916
I'm not getting on my fucking knees.

15:12.918 --> 15:14.004
These are good pants.

15:14.006 --> 15:15.237
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

15:15.240 --> 15:16.658
- Don't let him get away.
- Don't... Don't... Don't do it.

15:16.660 --> 15:17.877
D... Ah! Don't do it!

15:17.880 --> 15:19.401
[TIRES SCREECH]

15:19.403 --> 15:21.705
Who was that?

15:21.796 --> 15:24.101
Who was that?

15:24.103 --> 15:26.103
I'm guessing you weren't
first in your class.

15:26.105 --> 15:28.149
W-Which class?

15:28.151 --> 15:29.543
Any of 'em.

15:34.418 --> 15:37.027
[SNIFFS]

15:37.029 --> 15:38.550
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

15:38.552 --> 15:39.812
MAN: "I'm a married woman."

15:39.814 --> 15:43.294
Wo shi yigè yi hun de nurén.

15:43.296 --> 15:45.209
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

15:45.211 --> 15:47.951
"I'd love a glass of baijiu."

15:47.953 --> 15:51.085
Wo xiang yao yibei baijiu.

15:51.087 --> 15:53.913
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

15:53.915 --> 15:55.437
How much time you got?

15:55.439 --> 15:56.829
[FACET RUNS, STOPS]

15:56.831 --> 15:58.614
I got a few. Why?

15:58.616 --> 16:00.355
May want to ravage you.

16:00.357 --> 16:03.488
Haven't decided yet.

16:03.490 --> 16:05.142
You're trying to change the subject.

16:05.144 --> 16:06.493
What subject?

16:08.539 --> 16:11.279
Come on. It's too risky.

16:11.281 --> 16:14.108
Upping the dose a tad?

16:14.110 --> 16:16.588
To levels that caused
runaway growth in tumors

16:16.590 --> 16:18.373
and killed every primate test subject.

16:18.375 --> 16:19.939
It's a bit more than a "tad."

16:19.941 --> 16:23.508
That was before the Chinese
added our drug, Felix.

16:23.510 --> 16:26.903
The Zetacortex completely
stopped the tumors.

16:26.905 --> 16:29.210
The cocktail's safe.

16:29.212 --> 16:32.561
Well, there's a big difference
between primates and humans.

16:32.563 --> 16:35.390
"My husband is not home."

16:35.392 --> 16:39.089
Wo de zhangfu bu zaijia.

16:39.091 --> 16:42.136
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

16:42.138 --> 16:47.330
Alzheimer's, Parkinson's,
autism, epilepsy,

16:47.333 --> 16:51.145
depression, stroke,
encephalopathy, Tourette's.

16:51.147 --> 16:52.838
What if you cured them all?

16:52.841 --> 16:55.278
You just like wrapping
your mouth around big words.

16:55.281 --> 16:57.151
Hell, cured one of them?

16:57.153 --> 17:00.893
I mean, how many lives would
be altered for the good?

17:00.895 --> 17:02.460
We couldn't even quantify it.

17:02.462 --> 17:03.737
Come on, Cora.

17:03.740 --> 17:06.954
If, if, if.

17:06.958 --> 17:08.727
Yes, if, if.

17:08.729 --> 17:11.817
World history changes on "if."

17:11.819 --> 17:14.167
If you cured depression and Alzheimer's,

17:14.170 --> 17:15.760
just those two,

17:15.762 --> 17:18.784
you'd be mentioned in the
same company as Salk, Curie.

17:18.787 --> 17:21.871
I mean, we've only been trying
your cocktail for a year.

17:21.873 --> 17:23.481
There have been results.

17:23.483 --> 17:26.744
Yeah, itty-bitty, teeny-tiny ones,

17:26.747 --> 17:28.617
and no consciousness.

17:28.619 --> 17:32.447
In terms of regenerating brain
tissue, nothing's itty-bitty,

17:32.449 --> 17:36.494
and consciousness is a slippery thing.

17:36.496 --> 17:39.367
Brady Hartsfield is a gork, yes?

17:39.369 --> 17:41.291
Yes.

17:41.294 --> 17:43.806
So what's to lose here?

17:43.808 --> 17:46.374
[SIGHS] He's a human being.

17:46.376 --> 17:47.766
[CHUCKLING] Felix,

17:47.768 --> 17:49.942
he's a monster from a fairy tale

17:49.944 --> 17:52.252
that you would only
tell children you hate.

17:54.732 --> 17:56.569
I've already crossed too many lines.

17:56.572 --> 17:57.877
I can't cross another one.

17:59.394 --> 18:00.786
"Can't" or "won't"?

18:05.351 --> 18:09.005
Yeah, well, thank you very much.

18:09.007 --> 18:11.355
Yeah, just make sure you do.

18:11.357 --> 18:12.713
Yeah. Thanks.

18:12.716 --> 18:13.721
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

18:13.724 --> 18:15.229
Okay, you first.

18:15.231 --> 18:17.100
Mr. Dwight Cramm arrived

18:17.102 --> 18:19.842
and is flying his plane back to Texas.

18:19.844 --> 18:21.252
- Cha-ching!
- [CHUCKLES]

18:21.255 --> 18:22.760
Okay, so, um, Timothy Madden

18:22.763 --> 18:25.368
has four different Facebook
profiles that we know of...

18:25.371 --> 18:27.284
One under Madden, one under Ellis,

18:27.286 --> 18:28.487
one under Rackowski,

18:28.490 --> 18:30.593
and one under the name Edgar Segura.

18:30.596 --> 18:32.028
I can barely keep up.

18:32.030 --> 18:34.248
Okay, so the Segura page
and the Rackowski page

18:34.250 --> 18:36.032
both have comments
from the same person...

18:36.034 --> 18:37.346
Donald Madden

18:37.349 --> 18:41.080
of 12 Mayfield Street, East Bridgton.

18:41.082 --> 18:42.517
Relation?

18:42.519 --> 18:44.258
His brother.

18:44.260 --> 18:46.229
They always go home.

18:46.232 --> 18:50.394
[CHUCKLES] They always go home.

18:50.396 --> 18:52.701
[RESPIRATOR HISSING]

18:52.703 --> 18:55.271
[MONITOR BEEPING]

19:01.233 --> 19:02.916
Hey, Jon.

19:02.919 --> 19:04.309
Felix.

19:04.312 --> 19:06.584
So, we shuttered the
treatment center this morning.

19:07.935 --> 19:09.283
Oh, I'm sorry.

19:09.285 --> 19:10.460
I know what it meant to you.

19:12.041 --> 19:14.113
Can't justify a private
room and all this equipment

19:14.115 --> 19:16.072
for a gork with his history.

19:16.074 --> 19:17.557
He needs the room, Jon.

19:17.560 --> 19:19.684
The expenditures on the
vagus nerve stimulation,

19:19.686 --> 19:20.903
the increased oxygenation...

19:20.905 --> 19:22.339
Come on, my article in The Lancet...

19:22.341 --> 19:24.733
Was eight months ago. Nothing's changed.

19:24.735 --> 19:25.768
Look at this.

19:27.693 --> 19:28.822
Here.

19:28.825 --> 19:30.956
I'm telling you... That growth is real.

19:30.959 --> 19:32.393
You call that "growth"?

19:32.396 --> 19:34.396
This looks like inert tissue to me.

19:34.399 --> 19:35.961
There've been no changes on the EEG,

19:35.963 --> 19:38.137
no signs of mental activity.

19:38.139 --> 19:41.010
So this is about your
treatment center, is it?

19:41.012 --> 19:44.073
Jon, you know what
they say about junkies?

19:44.076 --> 19:45.467
Don't become a fucking junkie.

19:45.470 --> 19:49.472
But if we're to find a way
to boost neuroplasticity?

19:49.475 --> 19:51.823
We could bring the
brain-dead back from the dead.

19:51.826 --> 19:54.696
Hartsfield is bad PR and
a budgetary hemorrhage.

19:54.699 --> 19:56.895
He goes to Crestmore as soon
as a bed becomes available.

19:56.897 --> 19:59.213
And if, in the meantime,
he should die here,

19:59.216 --> 20:00.563
I'm ordering an autopsy...

20:00.566 --> 20:03.161
See what else you've been doing to him.

20:03.164 --> 20:04.990
My best to Cora.

20:04.992 --> 20:06.557
Cheers.

20:06.559 --> 20:08.820
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

20:08.822 --> 20:10.171
[WHISPERING] Asshole.

20:11.172 --> 20:12.911
[KEYS JINGLING]

20:12.913 --> 20:14.611
["BY THE SEASIDE" RINGTONE PLAYS]

20:17.612 --> 20:19.091
[CELLPHONE BEEPS, RINGTONE STOPS]

20:19.093 --> 20:20.713
Kermit!

20:20.716 --> 20:22.562
How's imminent retirement looking?

20:22.565 --> 20:24.320
Ah, better every day.

20:24.323 --> 20:25.288
Bullshit.

20:25.291 --> 20:26.971
You look scared shitless.

20:31.541 --> 20:34.411
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

20:34.413 --> 20:35.891
- Hey, Pete.
- [ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

20:35.893 --> 20:37.719
So, what's to miss about this job, huh?

20:37.721 --> 20:39.049
[LAUGHS]

20:39.052 --> 20:41.515
- Hi, Pete.
- Hey, Hol.

20:41.518 --> 20:43.083
So, what's up?

20:43.086 --> 20:45.624
I have the location of a
fugitive from justice for ya.

20:45.627 --> 20:46.690
Ah.

20:46.693 --> 20:48.773
Last time I checked, he
had 14 warrants out for him,

20:48.775 --> 20:51.167
one of them right here in Bridgton.

20:51.169 --> 20:52.777
Why don't you pick him up?

20:52.779 --> 20:54.083
No money in it.

20:54.085 --> 20:56.390
Be a nice feather in your cap, though.

20:56.392 --> 20:58.653
And you know he's still in the area?

20:58.655 --> 21:02.004
Holly does, and Holly's never wrong.

21:02.006 --> 21:03.312
Well, let me find a pen.

21:07.881 --> 21:09.228
[LIGHTER CLICKS]

21:09.230 --> 21:11.015
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

21:16.775 --> 21:18.963
Brings you by, stranger?

21:18.966 --> 21:20.370
Hey. How are you doin'?

21:20.372 --> 21:21.546
[SNIFFLES] P.T.

21:21.549 --> 21:23.591
It's been a year.

21:23.593 --> 21:26.376
Ah, I fucked up a disc
when I had my heart attack.

21:26.378 --> 21:28.073
I keep tweaking it.

21:28.075 --> 21:29.491
Fucking blast getting old.

21:29.494 --> 21:31.642
Tell me about it.

21:31.644 --> 21:33.557
You don't come visit him anymore?

21:33.560 --> 21:35.554
[SIGHS] Another bad habit I don't need.

21:35.557 --> 21:37.169
[LAUGHS]

21:37.171 --> 21:39.435
- Have a good one.
- You, too.

21:42.438 --> 21:44.869
So, Madden actually put up a fight?

21:44.872 --> 21:46.838
You don't look any worse for wear.

21:46.841 --> 21:49.355
[SCOFFS] I wouldn't go toe-to-toe

21:49.358 --> 21:51.227
with some macho idiot.

21:51.229 --> 21:53.098
That's a you move, not a me move.

21:53.100 --> 21:55.927
I could've tweaked a knee. [CHUCKLES]

21:55.929 --> 21:59.366
I had a uniform take him down,
some rookie CrossFit junkie.

21:59.368 --> 22:00.932
Boy didn't even break a sweat.

22:00.934 --> 22:02.580
Definitely time for you to retire.

22:02.583 --> 22:05.589
[SIGHS] With a huge
fucking smile on my face.

22:05.591 --> 22:07.548
[SCOFFS]

22:07.550 --> 22:10.466
Oh, oh. I almost forgot.

22:11.815 --> 22:12.893
Here.

22:15.035 --> 22:16.513
What?

22:16.515 --> 22:18.393
A receipt from a funeral home.

22:18.396 --> 22:22.432
Uh-huh, using a credit card
from a batch of stolen ones.

22:22.434 --> 22:25.957
That one is in the name of
Christopher Scott Gleason,

22:25.959 --> 22:29.570
but it was used by a David De La Cruz.

22:29.572 --> 22:30.962
Which affects me how?

22:30.964 --> 22:31.916
[LUMBER CLATTERS]

22:31.919 --> 22:33.643
David De La Cruz is a federal witness

22:33.646 --> 22:35.255
who slipped into the wind two months ago

22:35.258 --> 22:38.621
but is scheduled to testify in
federal court here in four days.

22:38.624 --> 22:41.244
Reward for his capture
is in the low six figures.

22:41.247 --> 22:43.670
Thank you. Why don't you want him?

22:43.673 --> 22:46.021
He's federal... Nothing to do with me.

22:46.023 --> 22:48.763
You did me a solid... I'm doing you one.

22:48.765 --> 22:50.417
[LUMBER THUMPS]

22:50.419 --> 22:51.992
You're helping me with this shit.

22:51.995 --> 22:54.135
Ah, I enjoy this shit.

22:55.641 --> 22:58.729
Nice evening. It's
gonna be a nice sunset.

22:58.731 --> 23:00.078
Plus beer.

23:00.080 --> 23:01.081
[LAUGHING] Yeah.

23:02.300 --> 23:04.151
[CLATTERS]

23:04.154 --> 23:05.757
You know, whoever built this did some...

23:05.760 --> 23:07.172
Some fine friggin' work.

23:07.174 --> 23:08.565
- Yeah.
- Geez.

23:08.567 --> 23:10.088
Ida did and her husband.

23:10.090 --> 23:11.916
[CHUCKLES]

23:11.918 --> 23:14.005
Why am I not surprised?

23:14.007 --> 23:15.830
Mm.

23:15.833 --> 23:17.705
A woman like that will live forever,

23:17.707 --> 23:19.402
'cause Death don't
want to deal with her.

23:19.404 --> 23:21.781
She'll have him vacuuming
five minutes after she's dead.

23:21.784 --> 23:23.080
[CHUCKLES]

23:23.083 --> 23:24.494
Or making pottery.

23:24.496 --> 23:26.156
Learning to speak Spanish.

23:26.159 --> 23:27.279
[CLATTERS]

23:27.281 --> 23:29.020
Doesn't Death already know Spanish?

23:29.022 --> 23:30.761
Ah, yeah, yeah, but she would have him

23:30.763 --> 23:32.159
perfecting his pronunciation.

23:32.162 --> 23:33.248
[SCOFFS] Yeah.

23:33.251 --> 23:35.286
- Rolling his "r's," eh?
- Uh-huh.

23:35.289 --> 23:37.420
[LAUGHING]

23:37.422 --> 23:38.421
Ah.

23:38.423 --> 23:39.903
[LUMBER CLATTERS]

23:41.666 --> 23:42.877
She's a good soul.

23:44.821 --> 23:46.126
She certainly is.

23:47.171 --> 23:49.901
What?

23:50.000 --> 23:51.392
What?

23:55.571 --> 23:58.006
I'm out. You got more?

23:58.008 --> 23:59.749
In the fridge.

24:00.924 --> 24:02.445
You want anything?

24:02.447 --> 24:03.881
Ah, another one of these.

24:03.883 --> 24:06.493
Will do.

24:06.495 --> 24:08.627
[SIGHS]

24:10.020 --> 24:11.978
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER P.A.]

24:15.416 --> 24:16.588
Hey.

24:16.591 --> 24:17.938
Hi.

24:17.941 --> 24:19.210
You called, I came.

24:19.213 --> 24:20.463
[SIGHS]

24:20.465 --> 24:22.077
Sushi's a nice touch.

24:22.080 --> 24:23.294
Mm.

24:26.253 --> 24:27.426
You want a drink?

24:27.428 --> 24:30.088
Yes, please.

24:30.091 --> 24:32.693
- [REFRIGERATOR DOOR OPENS]
- So, tell me. What happened?

24:32.695 --> 24:34.303
Your ex-boyfriend out there.

24:34.305 --> 24:35.854
Oh, please.

24:35.857 --> 24:39.177
I went on one date with
him three years ago... one.

24:39.179 --> 24:42.311
And then I met you, and all
was right with the world.

24:42.313 --> 24:44.313
Whatever the case,

24:44.315 --> 24:46.360
they told me they're
transferring Hartsfield.

24:49.276 --> 24:51.015
Transferring him where?

24:51.017 --> 24:52.628
Downstate. Crestmore.

24:53.846 --> 24:55.629
Hmm.

24:55.631 --> 24:58.849
- [BOTTLE OPENS]
- Well, karmically or coincidentally,

24:58.851 --> 25:00.590
I got a call from Liang this morning.

25:00.592 --> 25:02.636
He's wondering if
there's been any progress.

25:02.638 --> 25:04.640
No, none that I can see.

25:06.604 --> 25:10.339
Well, he insinuated that if
we can't show him something,

25:10.341 --> 25:12.907
then, uh, we're out of this experiment

25:12.909 --> 25:15.213
and some other doctor's in, so...

25:15.215 --> 25:17.999
baby, up the dose.

25:18.001 --> 25:19.304
Can I have some ginger?

25:19.306 --> 25:21.872
We can't.

25:21.874 --> 25:24.635
A little ponzu, too.

25:24.638 --> 25:26.660
[SIGHS] Look, if we stick
with the current dosage,

25:26.662 --> 25:29.010
in time, it will show further yield.

25:29.012 --> 25:31.621
The last dramatic
growth was six months ago

25:31.623 --> 25:33.231
in the temporal lobe,

25:33.233 --> 25:34.580
and since then zip.

25:36.410 --> 25:39.281
Caution and time...

25:39.283 --> 25:42.066
They're liabilities at this point.

25:42.068 --> 25:45.374
You got to dose that
motherfucker to the gills.

25:45.376 --> 25:49.552
If he lives, we're geniuses.

25:49.554 --> 25:51.118
And if he dies, he dies.

25:51.121 --> 25:53.774
I mean, there's really
nothing to lose here.

25:53.776 --> 25:55.993
[GROANS] What about my license,

25:55.995 --> 25:58.343
my reputation?

25:58.345 --> 25:59.823
Look, I...

25:59.825 --> 26:02.696
I respect you... You know that.

26:02.698 --> 26:04.917
You just need to respect me, okay?

26:11.620 --> 26:14.359
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

26:14.361 --> 26:16.407
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

26:21.325 --> 26:23.414
[CELLPHONE DIALS]

26:26.025 --> 26:29.202
["BY THE SEASIDE" RINGTONE PLAYS]

26:39.517 --> 26:41.386
Shit!

26:41.388 --> 26:48.872
♪ ♪

26:48.874 --> 26:51.135
Shit.

26:51.137 --> 26:53.096
[GRUNTING]

26:54.663 --> 26:56.750
Come on, come on, come on!

26:56.752 --> 26:58.795
Pete, come on!

26:58.797 --> 27:00.405
Come on!

27:00.407 --> 27:02.190
[COMPRESSIONS THUD]

27:02.192 --> 27:04.907
[IN SLOW MOTION] Come on, Pete, come on!

27:14.770 --> 27:16.210
Thanks, Ash.

27:18.425 --> 27:19.816
[VEHICLE DOORS CLOSE]

27:19.818 --> 27:26.780
♪ ♪

27:26.860 --> 27:34.048
♪ ♪

27:34.050 --> 27:35.658
[MUSIC FADES]

27:35.660 --> 27:36.790
Thanks.

27:36.792 --> 27:38.010
Mm-hmm.

27:49.492 --> 27:51.797
To your friend Pete.

27:51.807 --> 27:53.591
- [CUPS CLINK]
- Pete.

28:02.164 --> 28:04.817
He loved yoga.

28:04.820 --> 28:06.212
Excuse me?

28:08.910 --> 28:11.469
He hid it from everyone...

28:11.472 --> 28:13.565
Like the way other cops
would hide addictions

28:13.567 --> 28:17.569
or boyfriends or whatever.

28:17.571 --> 28:20.485
Drank this green juice...

28:20.487 --> 28:23.407
Equal parts kale and
Brussels sprouts and fuck all.

28:23.410 --> 28:25.012
Antioxidants, he'd tell me...

28:25.014 --> 28:27.797
Got to get them in every day.

28:27.799 --> 28:31.455
And yet... he died, anyway.

28:35.372 --> 28:37.646
Leaves me running around in
me little fucking sneakers,

28:37.649 --> 28:39.243
speed walking,

28:39.245 --> 28:40.767
healthy eating.

28:40.769 --> 28:42.360
What's the point of all that shit?

28:46.818 --> 28:50.037
[SNORTS]

28:50.039 --> 28:51.690
He told me he was gonna retire

28:51.692 --> 28:54.041
with a big fucking smile on his face.

28:54.043 --> 28:55.653
That was his retirement plan.

28:58.743 --> 28:59.788
And you?

29:01.964 --> 29:04.138
What?

29:04.140 --> 29:07.924
What's your retirement plan?

29:07.926 --> 29:09.422
- I...
- [CUPS CLATTER]

29:09.425 --> 29:12.450
I'm done... Working with Holly,

29:12.452 --> 29:16.761
building gazebos for
mad, ginger dynamo people.

29:22.854 --> 29:26.638
But isn't that more reacting to life

29:26.640 --> 29:30.514
instead of... living it?

29:31.907 --> 29:33.732
No. That is living.

29:33.734 --> 29:35.517
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

29:35.519 --> 29:36.735
[SIGHS]

29:36.737 --> 29:39.738
You... You have spent your entire life

29:39.740 --> 29:42.741
cleaning up other people's messes.

29:42.743 --> 29:45.876
What would you like?

29:45.879 --> 29:48.577
What do you want in the
time that's left to you?

29:52.449 --> 29:55.754
Fewer conversations like these.

29:55.756 --> 29:58.324
[BARKING CONTINUES IN DISTANCE]

30:04.330 --> 30:07.027
[INSECTS CHIRPING]

30:07.029 --> 30:08.726
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

30:15.951 --> 30:17.517
[FLOORBOARD CREAKS]

30:23.828 --> 30:25.438
[DOOR CREAKS]

30:29.724 --> 30:32.029
Why is there a goldfish in my house?

30:32.032 --> 30:34.837
